<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-281-537  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 281 537.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Jan 26 1989 n1102* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Prime dismisses new MAI disclosures. (Prime Computer, MAI BasicFour Inc.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Prime Computer Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)MAI Basic Four Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    MFB; PRM.andO;Topic:     TakeoversLegal IssuesDisclosureFinancingCourt Cases.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PRIME DISMISSES NEW MAI DISCLOSURES Prime Computer Inc quickly dismissed theadditional disclosures made by MAI Basic Four Inc to Prime shareholders asstill failing to meet Securities andamp; Exchange Commission disclosurerequirements, and that it will vigorously oppose any effort by MAI tooverturn a preliminary injunction issued by the Masshachusetts Federal Courtin December.andP;  Prime reckons that the disclosures are insufficient in theapplicability of the Federal Reserve Board margin requirements to thefinancing of the tender offer; and information on the full role of DrexelBurnham Lambert Inc in the financing of the tender offer.andP;  &quot;We believe MAI'sproposed financing through the sale of junk bonds and through bank loansraises serious questions under the Federal Reserve Board's marginregulations,&quot; Prime said.andP;  In general, the Federal Reserve Board marginregulations specify that when financing an acquisition, a company may notborrow more than 50% of the value of the outstanding shares of the company itis seeking to acquire, when the borrowing is secured by the stock of thecompany to be acquired.andM;MAI mailed the new information to Prime shareholders on Tuesday and filed inthe US District Court for Massachusetts to have the orders on it lifted.andO;</TEXT></DOC>